      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T16:45:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve got a target that needs build/build_config.h, but can\u0027t depend on base: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/crashpad/crashpad/+/2405650\n\nThe change causes gn check to fail because build/build_config.h is no longer in a dep of util:no_cfi_icall. There are also some errors because compat is including base/strings/string16.h without any dependency chain, though I\u0027m not sure why that\u0027s only failing now.\n\nI think we can create a separate target for build/build_config.h for everything to depend on, but I\u0027m wondering why Chromium doesn\u0027t apparently need to do that.",
      "parentUuid": "21ad0d9d_b31576e2",
      "revId": "1c77abe9095655e250713fef0996f1aa5c4c04b8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b20ad0c_1986734d",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 15
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T17:40:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, I think Chromium doesn\u0027t have a problem with this because gn check doesn\u0027t check includes of files which aren\u0027t known to the build, which is the case for build/build_config.h. Removing build/build_config.h from mini_chromium\u0027s base target avoids that error (but still investigating the errors for base/strings/string16.h)",
      "parentUuid": "b51078e7_4dae6adb",
      "revId": "1c77abe9095655e250713fef0996f1aa5c4c04b8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
